And here I am today, still serving him and living for him and doing all I can to reach others with a wonderful glorious message of his gospel.

45:44.750 --> 45:45.050
Amen?

45:45.811 --> 45:46.352
Come and pray.

45:51.499 --> 45:56.466
Lord Jesus, we thank you today for your supreme sacrifice on Calvary.

45:57.954 --> 46:15.179
And even though we have seen the horrible betrayal and the Judas kiss, but yet in your great love and mercy, you kept reading with Judas, giving him every opportunity to repent and to turn back, but he didn't.

46:15.200 --> 46:17.283
Lord, we thank you that you were merciful to us.

46:18.605 --> 46:24.193
We thank you that you prayed it with us, some of us for years before we finally surrendered to you.

46:25.174 --> 46:27.698
But we give you thanks for that, that today,

46:28.162 --> 46:37.235
that we're born again of your spirit, that we have gone through the door, and that we know you personally, and that you have made us fit for your heaven.

46:37.916 --> 46:39.598
You've given us your righteousness.

46:39.618 --> 46:43.103
You took our sins, and you gave us your righteousness and exchange.

46:43.423 --> 46:44.685
So we thank you for that.

46:45.927 --> 46:53.778
Help us now, Lord, as we look forward to next Sunday, God willing, to be in your house together as the family of God

46:53.954 --> 46:58.083
and to think of the wonderful, glorious, mighty resurrection.

46:59.165 --> 47:07.423
Lord, it's exciting to know because you rose again that we will live also and that we will rise again until life eternal.

47:08.164 --> 47:11.511
So we praise you and we give you thanks in Christ's name.

47:12.293 --> 47:12.754
Amen.

